g":"discharging-pilonidal-sinus-disease","fullItemName":"Scenario: Discharging pilonidal sinus disease"}]},{"id":"1dac71ef-a878-59d3-b800-7dd1d79f5cb1","fullItemName":"Supporting evidence","slug":"supporting-evidence","subChapters":[]},{"id":"5876a6ee-ac31-5275-a7f2-b3b3e513c1bb","fullItemName":"How this topic was developed","slug":"how-this-topic-was-developed","subChapters":[{"id":"22ce5599-2e29-5919-bd16-bf0617453826","slug":"search-strategy","fullItemName":"Search strategy"},{"id":"d8aa74b4-0c88-5852-9bcc-3817b5f86f5b","slug":"stakeholder-engagement","fullItemName":"Stakeholder engagement"},{"id":"9dd8ac08-630c-5212-a9d2-1d8f788d1caf","slug":"evidence-exclusion-criteria","fullItemName":"Evidence exclusion criteria"},{"id":"3070639d-61b1-577a-97fa-88d5441340c8","slug":"organizational-behavioural-financial-barriers","fullItemName":"Organizational, behavioural and financial barriers"},{"id":"39cd1f65-825c-5a34-9a8e-b7cc02681b0f","slug":"declarations-of-interest","fullItemName":"Declarations of interest"}]},{"id":"18c3993f-be17-501e-8c6e-eefd9c22eef1","fullItemName":"References","slug":"references","subChapters":[]}]},"parentChapter":{"id":"76719a1e-9f78-592f-85d1-ae71da6d9471","slug":"management","fullItemName":"Management"},"subChapters":[{"id":"882a296f-1a8e-5d56-8afe-e440601e6d49","slug":"management","fullItemName":"Management","depth":3,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 063ecbd9-5b5e-4f63-8141-240cffd488f7 --><h3>How should I manage asymptomatic pilonidal sinus disease?</h3><!-- end field 063ecbd9-5b5e-4f63-8141-240cffd488f7 -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item b054b66b-bdd9-4dd0-bbe7-e17d984b541b --><!-- begin field a82a31a9-83dc-4f4f-b5c1-5bd7b69b4bc5 --><ul><li><strong>If a person presents with <a class=\"topic-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pilonidal-sinus-disease/diagnosis/diagnosis/\">asymptomatic pilonidal sinus disease</a>:</strong><ul><li>Advise a 'watch and wait' approach, and reassure that treatment is not necessary.</li><li>Advise on meticulous perianal hygiene with regular baths or showers.</li><li>Provide patient information on pilonidal sinus disease<strong>. </strong>For example:<ul><li><a data-hyperlink-id=\"ff57c67e-2cff-4720-9303-aa3e00a9579f\" href=\"https://www.nhs.uk/conditions/pilonidal-sinus/\">Pilonidal sinus</a> published by NHS (<a data-hyperlink-id=\"1fc9f1ab-b68f-4d81-bba7-aa3701806117\" href=\"https://www.nhs.uk/\">www.nhs.uk</a>).</li></ul></li></ul></li></ul><!-- end field a82a31a9-83dc-4f4f-b5c1-5bd7b69b4bc5 --><!-- end item b054b66b-bdd9-4dd0-bbe7-e17d984b541b -->","subChapters":[{"id":"5ce8f355-7734-505d-a76c-d6e7f6d430e9","slug":"basis-for-recommendation-a47","fullItemName":"Basis for recommendation","depth":4,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 1f020bc4-03da-430f-88ee-44e0dbc2537d --><h4>Basis for recommendation</h4><!-- end field 1f020bc4-03da-430f-88ee-44e0dbc2537d -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item a47e462e-6fd2-4d05-8215-e3475ce53c58 --><!-- begin field 926e441f-2d52-40bd-b13f-23bf4adbcf93 --><p>These recommendations are based largely on <em>The treatment of pilonidal disease: guidelines of the Italian Society of Colorectal Surgery (SICCR)</em> [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pilonidal-sinus-disease/references/\">Segre, 2015</a>], the <em>German national guideline on the management of pilonidal disease</em> [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pilonidal-sinus-disease/references/\">Iesalnieks, 2016</a>], <em>The American Society of Colon and Rectal Surgeons’ Clinical Practice Guidelines for the Management of Pilonidal Disease</em> [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pilonidal-sinus-disease/references/\">Johnson, 2019</a>], evidence from a prospective case control study [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pilonidal-sinus-disease/references/\">Harlak, 2010</a>], and on expert opinion in review articles on pilonidal sinus disease<em> </em>[<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pilonidal-sinus-disease/references/\">Marza, 2013</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pilonidal-sinus-disease/references/\">BMJ, 2018</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pilonidal-sinus-disease/references/\">Kober, 2018</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pilonidal-sinus-disease/references/\">Choy, 2019</a>].</p><ul><li>Experts advise that asymptomatic pilonidal sinus disease should be treated by reassurance and hygiene [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pilonidal-sinus-disease/references/\">Segre, 2015</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pilonidal-sinus-disease/references/\">Iesalnieks, 2016</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pilonidal-sinus-disease/references/\">BMJ, 2018</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pilonidal-sinus-disease/references/\">Kober, 2018</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pilonidal-sinus-disease/references/\">Choy, 2019</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pilonidal-sinus-disease/references/\">Johnson, 2019</a>] because the disease often dissipates as the person passes the fourth decade of life [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pilonidal-sinus-disease/references/\">Choy, 2019</a>].</li><li>A prospective case control study that included 587 people with pilonidal sinus disease and 2780 healthy controls found that the risk of pilonidal sinus disease was higher in people who take two or less showers or baths per week compared with those who take three or more baths per week [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pilonidal-sinus-disease/references/\">Harlak, 2010</a>].</li><li>Expert opinion in a nursing review article is that people who have fewer than two baths a week are more at risk of developing pilonidal sinus disease, presumably due to the increased risk of bacterial proliferation in the natal cleft region [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/pilonidal-sinus-disease/references/\">Marza, 2013</a>].</li><li>The recommendation to provide patient information on pilonidal sinus disease<strong> </strong>is based on what CKS considers to be good clinical practice.</li></ul><!-- end field 926e441f-2d52-40bd-b13f-23bf4adbcf93 --><!-- end item a47e462e-6fd2-4d05-8215-e3475ce53c58 -->","subChapters":[]}]}]}}},"staticQueryHashes":["3666801979"]}